---

olive oil
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
1 sprig spring onion
1 packet chicken breast
1 tsp honey
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend

• Grate the carrot. Drain the sweetcorn. Thinly slice spring onion.
• Cut chicken breast into 1cm strips.
• SPICY! This spice blend is hot! Add less if you're sensitive to heat. In a medium bowl, combine chicken strips, Mexican Fiesta spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken and corn, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and toss to coat.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste and toss to combine.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Top each tortilla with slaw and Mexican chicken and corn.
• Drizzle over mayonnaise and garnish with spring onion to serve. Enjoy!